Enum EjbcaModuleTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EjbcaModuleTypes>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<EjbcaModuleTypes>, org.cesecore.audit.enums.ConstantType<org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleType>, org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleType

    public enum EjbcaModuleTypes
extends java.lang.Enum<EjbcaModuleTypes>
implements org.cesecore.audit.enums.ModuleType
    EJBCA specific security audit event module types, for audit using CESecore's audit log. A modules is a group of related functionality. These module types are part of EJBCA (not the core itself) and extend the list of already existing module types of CESeCore.
    See Also:
    ModuleTypes, EjbcaEventTypes, EjbcaServiceTypes
